<br>
I would like to point out that it has been stated that due to his RL, Trompen will not be able to camp RF for several months. So let's boil this down to what the &quot;real&quot; cost is:<br>
<br>
Trompen has a family and spent a week+ camping RF for his epic at the cost of his family life. Anyone that is married (and especially those with children) know how much resentment, anger, irritation, etc. this game can cause in a family, especially if the spouse doesn't play and hates the game. I know how I felt after having to deal with my wife's anger after trying to get a Vox raid together for hours on end, and then having to cancel it due to lack of turnout. I can't imagine what the situation in my household would have been like if I had spent a week thusly. Now, after this incident, Trompen will have to wait even *longer* before he can get his epic. Think about that for awhile.<br>
<br>
Beyond all these stupid game pixels, this is far worse. Apologies cost people nothing. They are mindless platitudes that only seem rarer online because anonymity breeds arrogance and a$$holes. SoT (and more importantly, SHEI) should camp RF for Trompen, let his guild know when he is up, and the whole server should let him stay up for as long as it takes for Trompen to log on and the forces to get there. That will make up for this. That will minimalize the impact on Trompen's real life, and show that SoT as a guild is sorry for their actions.<br>
<br>
I hope that people in SoT that either don't feel responsible, or barely feel sorry think about the human cost to Trompen, and how classy he has been about this. He hasn't flamed. He has accepted apologies in /tell. He hasn't harrassed SoT with outraged flame filled tells. He has shown the upmost restraint and class. He knows this is only a game. Does SoT?<br>
